whereas.text:
Whereas every day, Parkinson's disease greatly impacts millions of individuals in the United States
			 who  are caregivers, family members, and friends of individuals with
			 Parkinson's disease;

Whereas the economic burden of Parkinson’s disease is an estimated $14,400,000,000 each year,
			 including indirect costs to patients and family members of $6,300,000,000
			 each year;

Whereas although research suggests that the cause of Parkinson’s disease is a combination of
			 genetic and environmental factors, the exact cause and the exact
			 progression of the disease remain unknown;
